Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
update_glitch(25.10)                                      update_glitch(25.10)

Name
       update_glitch  -  Allows  you to run glitch analysis without running SI
       delay analysis

Syntax
       update_glitch

       [-help]

       [-effort {medium | high}]

       Allows you to run glitch analysis without running  SI  delay  analysis.
       This  command  provides  the  ability to run glitch analysis on all the
       nets in a design or on a subset of nets.

       Using the update_glitch command without report_timing or  update_timing
       will only run glitch analysis.

       Note:  It is not recommended to run the update_glitch command after the
       report_timing or update_timing command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each update_glitch parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:  man update_glitch.

       -effort {medium | high}
              Specifies the effort level for update glitch.

              When set to high, glitch analysis uses more accurate modeling of
              glitch for small attackers, thereby reducing pessimism.

              Note: The run time in high mode may be slightly higher,  and  is
              largely dependent on the distribution of coupling.

              Default: medium

       Examples
              * The  following command will run glitch analysis without SI de-
                lay:

                > update_glitch

Related Information
              * report_noise

              * report_timing

              * setSIMode

              * getSIMode

